The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 18: The government is likely to discuss three issues related to telecom tomorrow. On the agenda are the number of 3G players in a circle, the 2 per cent administrative fee proposed by Trai, and the revised spectrum charges ranging between 3 per cent and 8 per cent for telecom operators, a department of telecom official said.                             
	 London, Dec. 18: UK business secretary Peter Mandelson has said the Tatas have the first responsibility to ensure the survival of car brands Jaguar and Land Rover. According to him, it is too early to judge whether state help would be needed at Jaguar Land Rover, which employs around 15,000 in the UK.                            
	 Detroit, Dec. 18: Chrysler LLC will shut down all its manufacturing operations from the end of this week for at least a month because of credit crisis and dwindling sales. Meanwhile, General Motors said it had not reopened merger talks with Chrysler.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 18: HDFC Bank plans to raise around Rs 1,500 crore through the issue of upper and lower Tier-II bonds next week, the banks deputy treasurer, Ashish Parthasarathy, said.                             
	 London, Dec. 18: British Airways and Qantas Airways have failed to reach an agreement on the terms of a merger which could have helped them counter the current downturn in the industry.                                                                                                                         
